{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KPfiW4y8cUTLgN2CqqvFov","type":"tool_result","content":"commit 833d9ecb17e7251b6df1656c863e86c79950a43c\nAuthor: FiremanDecko (GKE Agent) <firemandecko@fenrir-ledger.dev>\nDate:   Sun Mar 15 04:03:04 2026 +0000\n\n    fix: resolve trial not starting on Google sign-in — issue:944\n    \n    Root cause: the fire-and-forget trial init fetch in the auth callback page\n    used the default keepalive:false, so browsers aborted the in-flight request\n    when window.location.replace() navigated away. This regressed #922 in\n    production where in-cluster Redis is slower than Vercel KV was, making the\n    race condition consistently trigger.\n    \n    Two-layer fix:\n    1. Add keepalive:true to the /api/trial/init fetch in callback/page.tsx so\n       the browser completes the request even after page navigation.\n    2. Add defense-in-depth auto-initialization in /api/trial/status/route.ts:\n       if no trial exists when status is checked, initTrial() is called before\n       computing the status. This fallback handles any future init failures and\n       ensures canceled Stripe customers can still start a trial (no Stripe\n       status check is performed in the trial flow).\n    \n    Tests: 14 new Vitest integration tests for POST /api/trial/status covering\n    auto-init, canceled-Stripe-customer AC, active/expired/converted states,\n    auth/validation/rate-limit edge cases (785 total passing).\n    \n    Fixes #944\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n .../src/__tests__/trial/trial-status-route.test.ts | 321 +++++++++++++++++++++\n .../frontend/src/app/api/trial/status/route.ts     |  19 +-\n .../frontend/src/app/ledger/auth/callback/page.tsx |   9 +-\n 3 files changed, 343 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8704cb95-a276-4615-86f1-ec7832e348ff","uuid":"304b9c5d-7066-4e73-ab33-c3b84390a1b4","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"commit 833d9ecb17e7251b6df1656c863e86c79950a43c\nAuthor: FiremanDecko (GKE Agent) <firemandecko@fenrir-ledger.dev>\nDate:   Sun Mar 15 04:03:04 2026 +0000\n\n    fix: resolve trial not starting on Google sign-in — issue:944\n    \n    Root cause: the fire-and-forget trial init fetch in the auth callback page\n    used the default keepalive:false, so browsers aborted the in-flight request\n    when window.location.replace() navigated away. This regressed #922 in\n    production where in-cluster Redis is slower than Vercel KV was, making the\n    race condition consistently trigger.\n    \n    Two-layer fix:\n    1. Add keepalive:true to the /api/trial/init fetch in callback/page.tsx so\n       the browser completes the request even after page navigation.\n    2. Add defense-in-depth auto-initialization in /api/trial/status/route.ts:\n       if no trial exists when status is checked, initTrial() is called before\n       computing the status. This fallback handles any future init failures and\n       ensures canceled Stripe customers can still start a trial (no Stripe\n       status check is performed in the trial flow).\n    \n    Tests: 14 new Vitest integration tests for POST /api/trial/status covering\n    auto-init, canceled-Stripe-customer AC, active/expired/converted states,\n    auth/validation/rate-limit edge cases (785 total passing).\n    \n    Fixes #944\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n .../src/__tests__/trial/trial-status-route.test.ts | 321 +++++++++++++++++++++\n .../frontend/src/app/api/trial/status/route.ts     |  19 +-\n .../frontend/src/app/ledger/auth/callback/page.tsx |   9 +-\n 3 files changed, 343 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
